Affiliation: Dept. of Computer Science, PennState University, University  Dept. of Computer Science, University of Bonn, 53117 Bonn, and International Computer Science Institute, Berkeley, California.  Dept. of Computer Science at Princeton University.  Dept. of Computer Science, Princeton University,  
Abstract: We prove an exponential lower bound on the size of (ternary) algebraic decision trees for the MAX Problem of finding maximum of n real numbers. This complements n 1 lower bound (cf. M. O. Rabin [R72]) on the depth of algebraic decision trees for this problem. The method yields also for the first time a lower size bound for a polyhedral decision problem MAX= of testing whether the ith number is the maximum among a list of n real numbers, and gives the first nonlinear size lower bound on algebraic decision trees for the selection problems. 
